Mauritius’s Trade Deficit Widens by 4% in January, Agency Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-03-22T07:28:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/mauritius-s-trade-deficit-widens-by-4-in-january-agency-says.html
Mauritius’s trade deficit widened
to 4.9 billion rupees ($172 million) in January from 4.7 billion
rupees a year earlier, the central Statistics Office said.  The Indian Ocean island nation’s imports increased by 12
percent to 10 billion rupees, while exports advanced by 19
percent to 5.1 billion rupees, the Port Louis-based agency said
in a statement on its website today.  India was the biggest source of imports, accounting for 24
percent of shipments, with  Europe  the main buyer of Mauritian
goods, led by the U.K. and France, the statistics office said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in  Port Louis  at 
